attachments.text:
FORMATION is an easy to use app that you use to
explore your workplace.

This tutorial explains FORMATION using FORMATION. Each step
in the tutorial is a FORMATION point and you can click on 
the links inside them to go to the next step.

Points are visible on the map and when you open them,
you can explore their content. The map allows you to pan
and zoom to the area you are interested in. You can also
use search to find things that you are looking for.

Next we'll show you how to create your own points.

Next we'll show you how to create your own points.

attachments.text:
Points are how you share information about things around you.

To create a new point:            
- Click the ADD button
- Chose "Point" in the Workspace Tools menu
- Give it a name

If you want, can customize it further
- customize the color, icon and shape of the point marker via the customize badge menu
- Add some content like an image, links, text, etc.

Next we'll show you how to create a task.

attachments.title: How to create a new point

attachments.text:
Tasks are a special type of point that you can use to coordinate
who needs to do what in your workplace. 
                                        
To create a new task:
 - Click the ADD button
 - Chose "Task" in the Workspace Tools menu
 - Write the task name, select a due date for the task, assign the task to the responsible person
 - (optional) Add attachments like an image, link, text or object to the task
 
 Next, we'll show you how to use the map.

attachments.text: Next, we'll show you how to create a meeting point.
attachments.htmlPreview: Next, we'll show you how to create a meeting point.

attachments.text:
Meetings are useful to plan to meet people at a certain place.

To create a new meeting:
- Click the ADD button
- Chose "Meet" in the Workspace Tools menu
- Write the meeting name, select a date and time for the meeting and select the attendees
- (optional) Add attachments like an image, link, text or object to the meeting

Next, we'll ask you for some feedback.
